==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}}

# The state of being [[negligent]]
# {{legal}} {{singulare tantum}} The [[tort]] whereby a duty of reasonable [[care]] was [[breach]]ed, causing [[damage]]: any conduct short of intentional or [[reckless]] action that falls below the legal standard for preventing unreasonable injury.
# {{legal}} {{uncountable}} The breach of a duty of care: the failure to exercise a [[standard of care]] that a [[reasonable person]] would have in a similar situation.

====Usage notes====
* The breach of a duty of care is one element of the tort of negligence, but is also called {{term||negligence}}; one must therefore take care to clarify what is meant.

